\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Six sequential Gibbs iterations for the bivariate normal. Each panel adds one iteration: green = $\theta _1 \mid \theta _2$ update, blue = $\theta _2 \mid \theta _1$ update, orange star = new sample, red triangle = starting point. The characteristic horizontal--vertical staircase emerges.}}{5}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
